parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear cradle bolts can cause the loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control, which can result in serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear cradle bolts break off while driving
causing the frame and transmission to drop
and the steering shaft to break; the vehicle becomes difficult to steer or loses control; the middle cradle cracks in half.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the front subframe can cause the loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or serious injury, and can also result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle wobbles while steering; the subframe on one or both ends corrodes
causing the steering column to break; the front subframe cracks or rusts
leading to separation of the lower control arm and loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty body panels and door handles can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The glove box fails; both doors break; inside sliding door handle breaks; outside door handle breaks; body panel is loose; water leaks inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty dashboard and interior components can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially lead to distractions while driving.
symptoms: The dashboard does not fit properly into slots due to design flaw; the dash board has popped up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become inoperative, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt will not retract back into position
the seat belt is loose
the seat belt has fully extended and won't retract
the seat belt is limp
the seat belt has to be held up with a stick.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the temperature gauge can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure, which can result in costly repairs, vehicle downtime, and potentially lead to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: The temperature gauge does not function properly
the engine overheats
the dashboard or gauges are damaged
the engine fails or seizes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure, which can result in costly repairs, vehicle downtime, and potentially lead to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: The water pump fails
coolant leaks
the engine overheats
the gasket needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine knock prior to recall can cause engine damage or failure, which can result in costly repairs, vehicle downtime, and potentially lead to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: The engine makes a knocking sound
the engine fails or seizes.
